            "heading": "FAQ"
          }
        },
        "accordion_item_bpJkt4": {
          "type": "accordion_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Why does the app not recognize my Plus subscription?",
            "answer": "<p>If your Plus subscription is not recognized in the app, you can restore it manually. Open the app and go to \"Settings\" → \"User Profile\" → \"Subscription\". On the subscription screen, scroll down and tap \"Restore Purchase\". The app will check whether the Apple ID or Google Play account currently logged in has an active subscription and, if so, activate Soundbrenner Plus on your current Soundbrenner account.</p>"
          }
        },
        "accordion_1": {
          "type": "accordion_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How to request a refund for the Soundbrenner Plus subscription?",
            "answer": "<p>We currently do not offer the ability to subscribe directly from us. Instead we rely on Apple & Google to sell our subscription, collect payments and provide customer support relating to the payments. Please note if you contact us, we are unable to refund the subscription - you will have to ask for a refund at the place of your purchase.</p><p>To make this easier for you, we’ve provided the instructions below:</p><p><strong>Request a refund if you subscribed via Apple:</strong></p><p>Simply follow the steps outlined by Apple here:</p><p><a href=\"https://support.apple.com/en-us/118223\">https://support.apple.com/en-us/118223</a></p><p><strong>Request a refund if you subscribed via Google:</strong></p><p>Simply follow the steps outlined by Google here:</p><p><a href=\"https://support.google.com/googleplay/answer/2479637\">https://support.google.com/googleplay/answer/2479637</a> </p>"
          }
        },
        "accordion_2": {
          "type": "accordion_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How to cancel the Soundbrenner Plus subscription?",
            "answer": "<p>We hate when we need to jump through a lot of hoops to cancel a subscription. Hence we made it easy and frictionless for you.</p><p>You can cancel auto-renewal of your Soundbrenner Plus subscription any time. Once you cancelled:</p><ul><li>You won't be charged again</li><li>You can still enjoy the subscription benefits until the next renewal would have been due</li></ul><p>We currently do not offer the ability to subscribe directly from us. Instead we rely on Apple & Google to sell our subscription, collect payments and provide customer support relating to the payments. Please note if you contact us, we are unable to cancel the subscription for you since we are not granted these rights by Apple and Google - you will have to cancel at the place of your purchase. Luckily this is very easy!</p><p><strong>Cancel if you subscribed via Apple:</strong></p><p>Simply follow the steps outlined by Apple here:</p><p><a href=\"https://support.apple.com/en-us/HT202039\">https://support.apple.com/en-us/HT202039</a> </p><p><strong>Cancel if you subscribed via Google:</strong></p><p>Simply follow the steps outlined by Google here:</p><p><a href=\"https://support.google.com/googleplay/answer/7018481\">https://support.google.com/googleplay/answer/7018481</a> </p>"
          }
        },
        "accordion_5": {
          "type": "accordion_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Does the app still support DAW synchronization?",
            "answer": "<p>Outside of Ableton Link we discontinued the DAW sync beta due to usability and reliability issues. Setup was often complex and time-consuming, and the wide range of DAWs, operating systems, and device combinations made it difficult to ensure a stable experience.</p><p>Our current focus is on introducing tempo changes in the app and continuing to make the metronome as powerful and reliable as possible.</p>"
          }
        }
